# {{NAME}}

A Helios allocator built on [`helios-allocator-sdk`](https://pypi.org/project/helios-allocator-sdk/). Scaffolded by `helios-allocator init`.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Install the package + the SDK from PyPI.
pip install -e .

# 2. Copy and fill in the environment.
cp .env.example .env
$EDITOR .env

# 3. Run the decision loop.
python -m {{NAME_SNAKE}}
```

The default ranker is a Sentinel-style `reputation × capacity × class-fit × binary fee-fit`. The whole point of writing your own allocator is to differentiate that score function — open `src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/allocator.py` and edit `_score`.

## On-chain setup

Once the allocator is running locally:

```bash
# Register on AllocatorRegistry. Allocator vault is created in the same tx.
helios-allocator stake top-up --amount 5000000000 \
    --rpc-url $KITE_RPC_URL --operator-pk $ALLOCATOR_OPERATOR_PK

# Tail the structured event log.
helios-allocator logs
```

## Build with Claude Code

This scaffold is set up so an AI coding agent can iterate on the
ranker and ship to the marketplace without changing any Helios code.

In your terminal:

```bash
claude "Open src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/allocator.py and rewrite _score to weight \
strategies whose 30d realised P&L is in the top quartile of their \
class. Use helios_allocator.helpers.* — do not import workspace deps. \
Add a unit test that pins the ranking under a fixed candidate list."
```

The repo's [`CLAUDE.md`](https://github.com/emark-cloud/helios/blob/main/CLAUDE.md) is the canonical operational guide for AI agents working on Helios; the SDK's invariants in particular live in `Helios.md §11` and `docs/allocator-guide.md`.

